Paper: hep-th/0103151

Date: 2001-03-19

Title: Bouncing Branes

Authors: Emil M. Prodanov (NCSR "Demokritos", Athens)

Comments: 6 pages, LaTeX

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B530 (2002) 210-217

Two classical scalar fields are minimally coupled to gravity in theKachru-Shulz-Silverstein scenario with a rolling fifth radius. A Tolmanwormhole solution is found for a R x S^3 brane with Lorentz metric and for a Rx AdS_3 brane with positive definite metric.